if you can't find one to buy..
you could make one from junk laying around a Vw welding type machine shop.

http://www.globalserve.net/~jrivers/pictures/vw-torque-mult2.jpg

you need a flywheel,, a way to mark and drill the bolt pattern for the hub..
I used a lathe,, but you can use other methods.
a socket,,
a gear from a starter

http://www.356registry.org/Tech/axle_nut_removal.html

